  "objectives": "Objectives –Introduce basic control and performance concepts through instrument maneuvers\r\nAccomplish the following:\r\nIntroduce the “control and performance concept” of attitude instrument flying as outlined in flying training directives. Apply this concept to flying basic instrument maneuvers and general basic aircraft control such as straight and level flight, climbs, descents, turns and airspeed changes.\r\nIntroduce basic cross-check as it relates to the control and performance concept.\r\nIntroduce the role of trim in facilitating precise control and performance flying.\r\nAccomplish all required maneuvers as early in the block as student proficiency allows.\r\nNote: If issued, students should bring their flight gear and practice strapping into the cockpit during these events.\r\nSpecial Syllabus Requirement — Practice instrument flight at airspeeds and configurations similar to the radar pattern, slowing and stabilizing to configure, and final approach while configured.",
